textAfterTable: Note: Jomo Kenyatta was Prime Minister of Kenya from its independence on 12 December 1963 to 12 December 1964 when he became President of the Republic. He was re-elected unopposed on 22 December 1969 and again in 1974. He died in office on 22 August 1978. Vice President Daniel arap Moi succeeded Kenyatta and the National Assembly elected him President on 10 October 1978. He was re-elected unopposed by the National Assembly in 1979, 1983, and 1988.   29 December 1992 Presidential Election Registered Voters 7,900,000 (approx.)
